The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 October is 92,136 (10,619.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 October, there were 4,595 new confirmed cases (529.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 October, there were 3,814 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 20% (781 extra cases).
